          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Hebrew</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>Monday, 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Shevat, 1854</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">(<date>February</date>)</p>
                              <p>Most treasured friend:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have no doubt you received my<lb/> last letter
                                        with the enclosed $3. of <persName>Isaac
                                        Gersom</persName><lb/> * and if it is not worth anything, I
                                        am returning<lb/> the receipt to you. I have already spoken with<lb/>
                                        <persName>Marx</persName>, and he promised to send it up to
                                        now,<lb/> he hasn't sent me even a stone. I think you<lb/>
                                        would be doing well to send a reminder to<lb/> both these
                                        gentlemen to send me the money. I<lb/> have also told you
                                        that you could set aside<lb/> several of your school books.
                                        The money for<lb/> those which you sent to
                                                  <persName>Bruger</persName>
                                        <add>?</add>, you will<lb/> receive at the beginning of next
                                        month. I am<lb/> enclosing a letter to <persName>Dr.
                                                  Lilienthal</persName>, which I ask<lb/> you to
                                        translate into English. My intention<lb/> and hope is only
                                        for the glory of Godâ€”to prove<lb/> through this letter the
                                        necessity for the second day<lb/> of the holidays. I
                                        positively request that you<lb/> permit it to appear this
                                        month. I have already<lb/>
                                        <del>sent</del> prepared an answer for him to his heretical
                                        questions,<lb/> that is to all the questions he directed to
                                        you. I<lb/> expect your answer by return mail.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">Most respectfully,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Dr.
                                        Illoway</persName>.</p>
                              <p>*Perhaps he thinks the<lb/> check is worthless.</p>
                    </body>
